// compiler/codegen/nvptx_p6_vec_div_test.hexa
// RFC 071 P4 N56 — vec-div source-to-silicon generalisation fixture
//
// @version 0.0.1
// @capabilities [pure]
// @phase("parse_only")
//
// This file is a TEST FIXTURE for F-RFC071-E2E-VEC-DIV-NUMERIC-EQ
// (RFC 071 §4 P4 follow-on to N50 vec_mul `097451f3`). Same kernel
// shape as nvptx_p4_vec_mul_test.hexa but with `/` instead of `*`.
//
// Probes whether `_nvptx_binop_mnemonic` in compiler/codegen/
// nvptx_target.hexa covers FP64 division. NVPTX has TWO div modes
// (PTX ISA §9.7.1.4): `div.rn.f64` (IEEE round-to-nearest, ~52-bit)
// and `div.approx.f64` (fast, ~24-bit). The current mnemonic table
// (lines 460-481, HEAD `e4f79e26`) handles only add/sub/mul (+ the
// mixed-precision RFC 068 P3 siblings) — `div` is expected to fall
// through to the `// RFC 055 055-P0 - unsupported binop` honest stub.
// This fixture surfaces that gap precisely.
//
// Kernel name is `vec_div` so the falsifier substring-checks
// `.visible .entry vec_div` and inspects body for `div.f64` /
// `div.rn.f64` / `div.approx.f64` mnemonic.
//
// `@phase("parse_only")` declares this file's role: input to the P4
// emit-driver, not a standalone test runner.

// ── The kernel (gpu/SPEC.md §2 — @gpu_kernel must return void) ───────

@gpu_kernel
fn vec_div(a: [f64], b: [f64], c: [f64], n: i64) {
    let gid = gpu_block_id_x() * gpu_block_dim_x() + gpu_thread_id_x()
    if to_i64(gid) < n {
        c[to_i64(gid)] = a[to_i64(gid)] / b[to_i64(gid)]
    }
}
